hopobject.body: Would you like a receipt? metoprolol succ stada 95 mg Despite the trickle of good news overseas, international investors have been concerned with slackening growth in China. Figures released by China's National Bureau of Statistics on July 8 showed that the Chinese economy grew at a 7.5 percent rate year-over-year in the second quarter, off from its nearly 8 percent pace in the final quarter of 2012. China may grow at a 7.6 percent rate next year, if economists are correct in their forecasts.
